Dia. 03 Black 1 and 3 Work
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
{\colortbl ;\red255\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par Against White \'a1\'e2, Black's dansu at 1 is a strong move.
\par If White connects at 2, Black plays at 3 and captures White in a nice way.
\par
\par White 4 is unavoidable and then \cf1\b White dies\cf0\b0  after Black's hane at 5. \cf1\b
\par \cf0\b0
\par If White plays at 5 instead of 4, Black plays at A and White is captured again.
\par
\par }
